00:31:20.520 --> 00:31:29.910
Let me just hit some things I think that you
want to take note of on this one.

00:31:29.910 --> 00:31:35.130
I guess the nose shape, we mentioned that
one already, reduces the drag.

00:31:35.130 --> 00:31:37.480
It also reduces the loads.

00:31:37.480 --> 00:31:41.340
We have to worry about the punch loads between
the SRB and the tank.

00:31:41.340 --> 00:31:45.950
And those aerodynamics are driven quite a
bit by that nose shape.

00:31:45.950 --> 00:31:51.470
The SRB locations fore and aft, there is some
adjustment that you can have in that, and

00:31:51.470 --> 00:31:58.140
those are all optimized that whenever we do
the aerodynamics that puts a minimum amount

00:31:58.140 --> 00:32:02.090
of load into the system.

00:32:02.090 --> 00:32:07.260
Orbiter instance angle, that's the angle between
the Orbiter and the external tank.

00:32:07.260 --> 00:32:11.600
It drives the stability of the configuration
to some degree.

00:32:11.600 --> 00:32:14.539
But, more than that, it drove the loads quite
a bit into the program.

00:32:14.539 --> 00:32:17.480
And that was optimized.

00:32:17.480 --> 00:32:25.230
Full span elevators, we use those to adjust
the pitching moments so we get minimum change

00:32:25.230 --> 00:32:31.700
required to trim the vehicle from the SRBs,
solid rocket boosters, and the SSMEs, the

00:32:31.700 --> 00:32:35.110
main shuttle engines.

00:32:35.110 --> 00:32:44.550
SSME, plume effects and the plume effects
from the SRB, that's the only thing that we

00:32:44.550 --> 00:32:54.230
